		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>You take the form of a treetop creature or another animal or insect that can easily traverse heights, taking to a perch unseen by your enemies.</i></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Daily âœ¦ Polymorph, Primal</b></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Minor Action</b><b> &#8226; </b>Personal</p><p><b>Effect:</b> You assume the form of a Tiny or Small beast or insect that can climb to great heights with ease until the end of the encounter, or until you end the effect as a free action. In this form, you gain a climb speed equal to your speed and a +5 power bonus to Stealth checks. Additionally, any time you fall, you treat the distance you fall as being 20 feet shorter for the purposes of determining falling damage. While in this form, you can't attack or use magic items. </p><p>Published in Dragon Magazine 382, page(s) 54. </p>",
